<dl id="n08131e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08131e">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08131e"> 131(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Halliday invents keyed bugle / Geo Macfarlan &mdash; cornopean</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>German Military Music</b> <font color="green">[by W. H. Grattan Flood]</font>: the <mark>invention of</mark> the Irishman, Joseph <mark>Halliday</mark>, in 1809, gave a complete scale to brass instruments. This was the <mark>key-bugle</mark>, patented by Halliday, in 1810 &hellip; As is well-known, the <mark>cornopean was invented by George Macfarlane</mark>, in 1833 <small> <a name="IS2feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IS2feb24"><cite title="source">Irish Statesman</cite></a> (2 February 1924) 658b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
